_Summary_

* When executing the API [/2.0/repositories/{username}/{repo_slug}/pullrequests/#/merge], if there are errors with the merge, it returns with an unreadable error.

{code}
{
  "type": "error",
  "error": {
    "message": "<django.utils.functional.__proxy__ object at 0xcbce310>"
  }
}
{code}

bq. In the context of a diff, we understand "ignore white space" to mean "ignore changes in white space that are irrelevant in the programs operation. Thus the difference between these two lines is ignored


{code:js}
> var x = "ignore whitespace in strings";

> var x="ignore whitespace in strings";
{code}

bq. But a difference in a string literal is significant in any diff.\\
For an example: &#x27;whitespace&#x27; to &#x27;white space&#x27;. Thus the diff between these two lines:


{code:js}
> var x = "ignore whitespace in strings";

> var x = "ignore white space in strings";
{code}

bq. should be displayed even when "Ignore whitespace" is turned on.
